enum SimServiceId
 

SimServiceId defines an enumeration for a certain service on SIM or USIM.

Enumerator:
SimServiceChv1Disable  Chv1 disabling functionality (SST=1,UST=undef).
SimServiceAdn  ADN phonebook (SST=2,UST=1).
SimServiceFdn  FDN phonebook (SST=3,UST=2 and EST=1).
SimServiceBdn  BDN phonebook (SST=31,UST=6 and EST=2).
SimServiceMsisdn  MSISDN phonebook (SST=9,UST=21).
SimServiceLnd  LND phonebook, (SST=13).
SimServiceSms  SMS (SST=4,UST=10).
SimServiceAoc  Advice of Charge (SST=5,UST=13).
SimServicePrefPlmn  Plmn Selector (SST=7).
SimServicePlmnwAct  Plmn Selector (SST=43,UST=7).
SimServiceSmsParameter  Sms Parameters (SST=12,UST=12).
SimServiceSdn  SDN phonebook (SST=18,UST=4).
SimServiceCbmi  CBMI (SST=14,UST=15).
SimServiceCbmiRanges  CBMI-Ranges (SST=30,UST=16).
SimServiceSpn  Service Provider Name (SST=17,UST=19).
SimServiceImages  Images (SST=39,UST=22).
SimServiceMexe  Mexe (SST=49,UST=41).

Variable Documentation

const INT c_max_customizable_codes = 1
 

EccProvider is the provider to retrieve the ECC entries from the sim (GSM 11.11 V8.2.0 10.3.27). An instance of this class is part of the the Apoxi Data Control. A pointer to this provider can be retrieved from the main provider via the id:

c_ecc_provider_id

Following column id is defined: c_ecc_id WStringType: returns the number of the emergency call code as string. c_ecc_category_id NumberType: returns the category byte. The wrapper class EccCategory can be used to allow access to the category bits. c_ecc_source_id NumberType: returns the source from where the ECC was retrieved. This value shall be casted to the enumeration EccSource. c_ecc_phonenumber_id PhoneNumberType: returns the ecc code as an phonenumber object. c_ecc_sim_network_cnt_id NumberType: returns the number of ecc codes on SIM and Network, row value 0 shall be used.

for UMTS additional: c_ecc_alpha_id WStringType: returns the alpha identifier.

NOTE: Please do not instantiate this class.
